Package io.orchestrate.client

A high performance, asynchronous Java client to query the Orchestrate.io service.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    OrchestrateFuture<T>
    A listenable future, based on Future.
    OrchestrateFutureListener<T>
    Listens to the result of a OrchestrateFuture.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Client
    A client used to read and write data to the Orchestrate.io service.
    Client.Builder
    Builder used to create Client instances.
    DeleteOperation
    A delete operation to the Orchestrate.io service.
    Event<T>
    A container for the event and its associated KV data.
    EventFetchOperation<T>
    Fetch events for a key in the Orchestrate.io service.
    EventStoreOperation
    Store an event to a key in the Orchestrate.io service.
    JacksonMapper
    A utility object to configure a Jackson JSON ObjectMapper.
    JacksonMapper.Builder
    Builder used to create JacksonMapper instances.
    KvFetchOperation<T>
    Fetch an object by key from the Orchestrate.io service.
    KvMetadata
    A container for metadata about a KV object.
    KvObject<T>
    A container for a KV object.
    KvStoreOperation
    Store an object by key to the Orchestrate.io service.
    RelationFetchOperation
    Fetch objects related to a key in the Orchestrate.io service.
    RelationStoreOperation
    Store a relationship between two objects in the Orchestrate.io service.
    Result<T>
    A container for the search result and its associated KV data.
    SearchOperation<T>
    Search for data from the Orchestrate.io service.
    SearchOperation.Builder<T>
    Builder used to create SearchOperations.
    SearchResults<T>
    A container for the results from a search query.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ClientException
    An object that represents a failure to send a request from the Client.
    RequestException
    An object that stores information about a failed Client request.

Package io.orchestrate.client Description

A high performance, asynchronous Java client to query the Orchestrate.io service.

A User Guide for the client can be found at: http://orchestrate-io.github.io/orchestrate-java-client/
